4.41	Flag_of_Greenland	Flag of Greenland	The flag of Greenland was designed by Greenland native Thue Christiansen. It features two equal horizontal bands of white (top) and red with a large disk slightly to the hoist side of centre. The top half of the disk is red, the bottom half is white. The entire flag measures 18 by 12 parts; each stripe measures 6 parts; the disk is 8 parts in diameter, horizontally offset by 7 parts from the hoist to the centre of the circle, and vertically centered.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/09/Flag_of_Greenland.svg/225px-Flag_of_Greenland.svg.png
